                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d554">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">882.515/76: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Chargé in Liberia</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Hibbard</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-09-26T14:00:00-04:00"
                            >September 26, 1942—2 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>236. Your 291, September 9, 6 p.m., your 287, September 3, 5 p.m., and your
                    784–A, September 3.<note n="76" xml:id="d554fn76">Despatch No. 784–A not
                        printed.</note> You may advise the Liberian Government that in view of their
                    confirmation of the agreement for the acquisition of British current coin in
                    Liberia as contained in the Department’s telegram 187, August 3, 8 p.m., the
                    Treasury Department considers such agreement to have been approved by the
                    Liberian Government and to be in full force and effect.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
